{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "True Riches"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 7"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When you sit down to dine with a ruler, consider carefully what is set before you,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and put a knife to your throatif you possess a great appetite."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not crave his delicacies, for that food is deceptive."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 8"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not wear yourself out to get rich; be wise enough to restrain yourself."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When you glance at wealth, it disappears, for it makes wings for itself\nand flies like an eagle to the sky."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 9"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not eat the bread of a stingy man, and do not crave his delicacies;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for he is keeping track, inwardly counting the cost."
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Eat and drink,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "he says to you, but his heart is not with you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You will vomit up what little you have eaten and waste your pleasant words."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 10"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not speak to a fool, for he will despise the wisdom of your words."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 11"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not move an ancient boundary stoneor encroach on the fields of the fatherless,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for their Redeemer is strong; He will take up their case against you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 12"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Apply your heart to instruction and your ears to words of knowledge."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 13"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not withhold discipline from a child; although you strike him with a rod, he will not die."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Strike him with a rod, and you will deliver his soul from Sheol."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 14"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, if your heart is wise, my own heart will indeed rejoice."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My inmost being will rejoicewhen your lips speak what is right."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 15"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not let your heart envy sinners, but always continue in the fear of the LORD."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For surely there is a future, and your hope will not be cut off."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 16"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Listen, my son, and be wise, and guide your heart on the right course."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not join those who drink too much wineor gorge themselves on meat."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the drunkard and the glutton will come to poverty, and drowsiness will clothe them in rags."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 17"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Listen to your father who gave you life, and do not despise your mother when she is old."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Invest in truth and never sell it—in wisdom and instruction and understanding."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The father of a righteous man will greatly rejoice, and he who fathers a wise son will delight in him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "May your father and mother be glad, and may she who gave you birth rejoice!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 18"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, give me your heart, and let your eyes delight in my ways."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For a prostitute is a deep pit, and an adulteress is a narrow well."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Like a robber she lies in wait and multiplies the faithless among men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 19"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who has woe? Who has sorrow? Who has contentions? Who has complaints?\nWho has needless wounds? Who has bloodshot eyes?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Those who linger over wine, who go to taste mixed drinks."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not gaze at wine while it is red, when it sparkles in the cup\nand goes down smoothly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "In the end it bites like a snake and stings like a viper."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Your eyes will see strange things, and your mind will utter perversities."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You will be like one sleeping on the high seasor lying on the top of a mast:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "They struck me, but I feel no pain! They beat me, but I did not know it! When can I wake upto search for another drink?",
          "speaker": "Drunkard/Addicted Person"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}